docs.abstract: The group will create a political action committee and may be active in Democratic primaries. It is also planning to organize pro-Israel Democrats in early nominating states for 2020.
docs.snippet: The group will create a political action committee and may be active in Democratic primaries. It is also planning to organize pro-Israel Democrats in early nominating states for 2020.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Several prominent veteran Democrats, alarmed by the party’s drift from its longstanding alignment with Israel, are starting a new political group that will try to counter the rising skepticism on the left toward the Jewish state by supporting lawmakers and candidates in 2020 who stand unwaveringly with the country.

headline.main: Prominent Democrats Form Pro-Israel Group to Counter Skepticism on the Left
headline.print_headline: Veteran Democrats Form Group to Support Israel

docs.abstract: President Trump’s divisive behavior on race has pushed Democrats to try to set an example by confronting misconduct in their ranks and elevating the importance of identity and equality in politics.
docs.snippet: President Trump’s divisive behavior on race has pushed Democrats to try to set an example by confronting misconduct in their ranks and elevating the importance of identity and equality in politics.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The irony was difficult to miss: on the same day that racist images surfaced from Gov. Ralph Northam’s medical school yearbook page, Senator Cory Booker announced his bid to become the nation’s second black president and entered what is the most diverse campaign field in history.

headline.main: Trump Behaves One Way on Race. Democrats Demand Better From Their Own.
headline.print_headline: Pushed by Trump, Democrats Try to Set Example

docs.abstract: The Massachusetts senator, who has campaigned against wealth inequality, remains fairly wealthy herself, though well behind several other senators.
docs.snippet: The Massachusetts senator, who has campaigned against wealth inequality, remains fairly wealthy herself, though well behind several other senators.
docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren, the Massachusetts Democrat running for president, received a $300,000 book advance for her latest book, “This Fight Is Our Fight,” according to financial disclosure forms filed with federal elections officials on Tuesday.

headline.main: Elizabeth Warren Disclosure Forms Show $300,000 Book Advance, Other Assets
headline.print_headline: A Senator  Is Wealthy,  Just Less So Than Others

docs.abstract: Attorney General Mark Herring, like Gov. Ralph Northam, said he dressed in blackface years ago. And a woman came forward to describe being sexually assaulted by the lieutenant governor.
docs.snippet: Attorney General Mark Herring, like Gov. Ralph Northam, said he dressed in blackface years ago. And a woman came forward to describe being sexually assaulted by the lieutenant governor.
docs.lead_paragraph: RICHMOND, Va. — The third-ranking elected official in Virginia, Attorney General Mark R. Herring, acknowledged Wednesday that he had worn blackface at a party as an undergraduate student, deepening a crisis that has engulfed the state’s Democratic leadership.

headline.main: Second Virginia Democrat Says He Wore Blackface, Throwing Party Into Turmoil
headline.print_headline: Crisis in Virginia Grows, Tangling 3rd Top Official

docs.abstract: Mr. Biden is trying to stay above the intraparty fray, invoking his years with Obama. Mr. Sanders is taking direct aim at the former vice president.
docs.snippet: Mr. Biden is trying to stay above the intraparty fray, invoking his years with Obama. Mr. Sanders is taking direct aim at the former vice president.
docs.lead_paragraph: MONTICELLO, Iowa — On his first trip to Iowa in his third bid for the presidency, Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Tuesday accused President Trump of coddling white supremacists, called former President Barack Obama “an extraordinary man” and vowed fidelity to longstanding Democratic priorities like Medicare and increasing the minimum wage.

headline.main: Sanders and Biden Circle Each Other, Using Different Rules of Engagement
headline.print_headline: Different Game Plans for Biden and Sanders

docs.abstract: The longstanding verity that Americans vote with their pocketbook may be tested in the presidential election like never before, as Trump injects cultural and identity issues into the race.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The unemployment rate is at a 50-year low, companies are adding jobs and the gross domestic product grew by 3.2 percent in the first quarter, undercutting predictions of a coming recession.

headline.main: Abortion Fight or Strong Economy? For G.O.P., Cultural Issues Undercut 2020 Message
headline.print_headline: G.O.P. Worry: Hot Economy Is a Cold Topic

docs.abstract: The recovery, which has brought low unemployment and rising wages elsewhere, hasn’t really lifted industrial northeast Ohio. But President Trump has lost little of his support there.
docs.snippet: The recovery, which has brought low unemployment and rising wages elsewhere, hasn’t really lifted industrial northeast Ohio. But President Trump has lost little of his support there.
docs.lead_paragraph: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio — In May 2016, David Betras, a Democratic Party leader in the heart of industrial northeast Ohio, sent a memo warning Hillary Clinton’s campaign that it was on the verge of losing Ohio, Pennsylvania and Michigan because she was not connecting with blue-collar voters. These states “should be easy wins for us,’’ he wrote.

headline.main: There’s No Boom in Youngstown, but Blue-Collar Workers Are Sticking With Trump
headline.print_headline: A Blue-Collar City Sticks With Trump

docs.abstract: Mr. Beshear, the son of the state’s former governor, will face Matt Bevin, who survived a closer-than-expected vote on the Republican side.
docs.snippet: Mr. Beshear, the son of the state’s former governor, will face Matt Bevin, who survived a closer-than-expected vote on the Republican side.
docs.lead_paragraph: Kentucky Democrats on Tuesday nominated the state’s attorney general, Andy Beshear, to run against embattled Gov. Matt Bevin, who fended off a surprisingly strong challenge in a Republican primary that illustrated his general election vulnerability.

headline.main: Andy Beshear Wins Democratic Primary for Kentucky Governor

docs.abstract: In 1969, three college students in New Jersey built a network of 10,000 volunteers to lower the voting age. Now, campaigns are sprouting up again.
docs.snippet: In 1969, three college students in New Jersey built a network of 10,000 volunteers to lower the voting age. Now, campaigns are sprouting up again.
docs.lead_paragraph: JAMESBURG, N.J. — Stuart Goldstein still has the red-and-white bumper stickers and other artifacts from 1969, when he helped persuade New Jersey lawmakers that 18-year-olds should be able to vote.

headline.main: 16-Year-Olds Want a Vote. Fifty Years Ago, So Did 18-Year-Olds.
headline.print_headline: A Voter at 16? A Seed Planted 50 Years Ago Sprouts Anew

docs.abstract: Ms. Abrams declined to challenge Senator David Perdue, one of President Trump’s chief allies in Congress. She had been courted aggressively by national Democrats to run.
docs.snippet: Ms. Abrams declined to challenge Senator David Perdue, one of President Trump’s chief allies in Congress. She had been courted aggressively by national Democrats to run.
docs.lead_paragraph: Stacey Abrams announced on Tuesday that she would not run for Senate in 2020, denying Democrats their favored recruit for the race in Georgia. She did not say if she planned to run for president, which she has also been considering doing.

headline.main: Stacey Abrams Will Not Run for Senate in 2020
headline.print_headline: Abrams Won’t Run for Senate in Georgia
